@startuml preconditions-overview
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #555555

title dev-workgraph — Preconditions: overview & dependencies

legend top left
  **Preflight** runs before `run` (optional standalone: `check`)
  **Per-repo preconditions** must be satisfied before pipeline stages
endlegend

rectangle "Preflight (global)" #E3F2FD {
  card "**check**" as CHECK
}

rectangle "Per repository" #FFF8E1 {
  card "**authors**" as AUTH
  card "**init**" as INIT
  card "**init:period**" as INITP
}

rectangle "Downstream stages" #E8F5E9 {
  card "evidence" as EVID
  card "summarize" as SUM
  card "commit-group" as CG
  card "report" as REP
  card "prepare" as PRE
  card "final" as FIN
}

CHECK -down-> INIT : **run** preflight\n(abort if Ollama not ready)

AUTH -down-> EVID : **required**\nonly selected emails extracted
INIT -down-> SUM : **required** for full\nproject context in LLM
INIT -down-> CG
INIT -down-> REP
INIT -down-> PRE
INIT -down-> FIN

FIN ..> PRE : optional\nprior Q&A (extension)
FIN ..> FIN : extension mode\n(latestFinish chain)

INITP .up.> INIT : inherits repo-level\nproject.json by default
INITP -down-> SUM : same as init,\nscoped to periods/<id>/

note bottom of AUTH
  May run **without init**
  (evidence works, but no role/story grounding yet)
end note

note bottom of INIT
  May run **without authors**
  (but evidence still needs authors before export)
end note

note as NCTX
  **Project context block** (from init → project.json)
  injected into every LLM call after init:
  • role
  • story.preparedContext
  • profile (summary, domains, apparentStack, keyThemes)
  Missing project.json → CLI warns, continues with empty context
end note
INIT .. NCTX

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-check
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E3F2FD

title **check** — Ollama preflight (§14)

start

:Resolve Ollama base URL\n(default http://127.0.0.1:11434,\noverride with --url);

:GET /api/tags → list installed models;

if (Ollama reachable?) then (no)
  if (ollama binary on PATH?) then (yes)
    :Print: start server\n`ollama serve`;
  else (no)
    :Print OS-specific install help;
    note right
      **macOS:** brew install ollama
      **Linux:** curl … install.sh | sh
      **Then:** ollama pull <model>
      Suggested: qwen2.5-coder:14b, gpt-oss:latest
    end note
  endif
  #Pink:Exit code 1;
  stop
else (yes)
endif

if (≥ 1 model installed?) then (no)
  #Pink:Print pull suggestions;\nExit code 1;
  stop
else (yes)
  :Print installed model list;
endif

:Read ~/.workgraph/config.json → ollama slots;

partition "Validate saved preferences" {
  :Check **commitModel**;
  :Check **reportModel**;
  :Check **narrativeModel**;
  if (Any saved model NOT in installed list?) then (yes)
    #Pink:Warn + suggest `ollama pull`;\nExit code 1;
    stop
  else (no)
  endif
}

#LightGreen:✅ Ready;
note right
  **Standalone:** `dev-workgraph check`
  **In run:** `ollamaReady()` preflight — aborts
  before gathering inputs if not ready
end note

stop

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-authors
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF8E1

title **authors** — Author selection (§1)\nPrecondition for **evidence**

start

:Resolve repository path\n(relative → absolute);

:`git log --all --no-merges`\nAggregate authors **by email** + commit counts;

if (No commits?) then (yes)
  :Print "No commits found";
  stop
else (no)
endif

if (--json flag?) then (yes)
  :Print { repo, authors[] };\nNo save;
  stop
else (no)
endif

partition "Default pre-selection" {
  :Load saved selectedAuthors[]\nfrom config.json (if any);
  :Add git user.email from repo config\nif it appears in author list;
  note right
    Lesson from real runs: near-identical emails
    (vzaharchenko@… vs vzakharchenko@…)
    are easy to confuse — picker shows commit counts
  end note
}

if (--email <addr>… flag?) then (yes)
  :Match against known authors;\nWarn on unknown emails;
  if (Any matched?) then (no)
    stop
  else (yes)
  endif
else (no)
  :Interactive **checkbox** prompt\n"Select identities that are YOUR work";
  note right
    Each choice:
    Name <email>  (N commits)
  end note
  if (Nothing selected?) then (yes)
    stop
  else (no)
  endif
endif

:Persist to **~/.workgraph/config.json**;
note right
  repos["/abs/path/to/repo"].selectedAuthors = [
    "me@example.com", …
  ]
end note

#LightGreen:✅ Authors saved;

floating note left
  **Without authors:** evidence cannot know which commits are yours
  **Bots filtered by user choice:** Renovate, Dependabot, Snyk, teammates
  **May run without init** — independent precondition
end note

stop

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-init
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7

title **init** — Project initialization (§0)\nPrecondition for **summarize**, **commit-group**, **report**, **prepare**, **final**

start

:Resolve repository path;

if (--period / init:period mode?) then (yes)
  :Resolve period label + [from, to)\nPersist in config.json → periods.<id>;
  note right
    ISO YYYY-MM-DD, half-open **[from, to)**
    Label: letters, digits, . _ -
  end note
  -> period_branch;
else (no)
endif

:Target file:\n~/.workgraph/data/repos/<repo-id>/project.json\n(or periods/<id>/project.json);

if (project.json exists?) then (yes)
  :Skip (idempotent);
  stop
else (no)
endif

label period_branch
if (period mode?) then (yes)
  if (repo-level project.json exists?) then (no)
    #Pink:Error: run repo-level init first;
    stop
  else (yes)
    :**Copy** repo-level → periods/<id>/project.json\n(no LLM);
    #LightGreen:✅ Period inherited context;
    stop
  endif
else (no — full init)
endif

partition "Interactive inputs (H)" {
  :**Developer role** — select or --role;
  note right
    Principal Developer
    Staff Developer
    Senior Developer
    Junior Developer
  end note
  :Persist role → config.json;

  :**Project story** — editor or --story;
  note right
    Free-form, multi-line:
    • what the project is
    • how it started
    • pivots / milestones
    Raw human context — not evidence
  end note
}

partition "Automatic inputs (D)" {
  :Read **README.md** from repo root\n(if missing → continue, not an error);
}

:Pick **narrativeModel** (Ollama)\n--model overrides;\nsaved in config.ollama.narrativeModel;

partition "LLM session 1 — Prepare story (M:n)" {
  :Input: role + raw story;
  :Output: **story.preparedContext**;
  note right
    Role-adjusted reframing:
    • Principal → system boundaries, cross-cutting decisions
    • Staff → subsystem ownership, platform direction
    • Senior → feature ownership, product driver
    • Junior → assigned vs self-directed, learning scope
    Raw story kept unchanged
  end note
}

partition "LLM session 2 — Project profile (M:n)" {
  :Input: role + preparedContext + README;
  :Structured JSON output;
  :Output: **profile**;
  note right
    • summary — what project appears to be about
    • domains[]
    • apparentStack[]
    • keyThemes[]
    Interpretation, not proof
  end note
}

:Write **project.json**;
note right
  {
    role, story: { raw, preparedContext },
    readme: { present, path? },
    profile: { summary, domains, … },
    provenance: { model, generatedAt }
  }
end note

#LightGreen:✅ Project initialized;

stop

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-init-sequence
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title **init** — LLM sessions & data flow

actor "Developer" as DEV
participant "CLI\ninit" as CLI
database "Git repo" as REPO
database "config.json" as CFG
database "project.json" as PJ
participant "Ollama\n(narrativeModel)" as LLM

DEV -> CLI : dev-workgraph init ./repo\n[--role] [--story]\n[--period] [--from] [--to]

CLI -> REPO : resolve path → repo-id
CLI -> CFG : read/write role\n(and period definition if --period)

alt project.json exists
  CLI --> DEV : skip (idempotent)
else period && repo-level project.json exists
  CLI -> PJ : copy repo-level → periods/<id>/project.json
  CLI --> DEV : inherited (no LLM)
else full init
  DEV -> CLI : role (prompt or --role)
  CLI -> CFG : persist role
  DEV -> CLI : project story (editor or --story)
  CLI -> REPO : read README.md (optional)

  CLI -> LLM : **Session 1** — story prepare\n(role + raw story)
  LLM --> CLI : preparedContext

  CLI -> LLM : **Session 2** — project profile\n(role + preparedContext + README)\nJSON schema validated
  LLM --> CLI : profile { summary, domains, stack, themes }

  CLI -> PJ : write project.json + provenance
  CLI --> DEV : ✅ initialized
end

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-init-period
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #888888

title **init:period** / **init --period** — Review period seeding (§0.5)

start

:Define period in config.json;
note right
  periods: {
    "2022": { from: "2022-01-01", to: "2023-01-01" },
    "2022-H1": { from: "2022-01-01", to: "2022-07-01" }
  }
  Half-open [from, to) — no double-count on boundary
end note

:Data subtree (mirrors repo layout):
periods/<id>/project.json
periods/<id>/commits/ … groups/ … reports/ …;

if (repo-level project.json?) then (missing)
  #Pink:Error — run `init` first;
  stop
else (exists)
  :Copy repo-level → periods/<id>/project.json;
  note right
    No LLM — role/story rarely change between periods
  end note
endif

:Downstream stages use --period <id>;
note right
  • Load period project.json, fallback to repo-level
  • evidence filters commits by author timestamp ∈ [from, to)
  • final → RECONSTRUCTION.<project>.<period>.md
  • Period data travels with export/import
end note

#LightGreen:✅ Period ready;

stop

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-project-context
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

title **Project context block** — output of preconditions, input to all later LLM steps

package "Sources" {
  [config.json\nrole] as ROLE
  [project.json\nstory.preparedContext] as STORY
  [project.json\nprofile] as PROF
}

package "Project context block\n(prepended to prompts)" as BLOCK {
  component "Role" as R
  component "Prepared story context" as PS
  component "Profile summary" as SUM
  component "Domains" as DOM
  component "Apparent stack" as STK
  component "Key themes" as THM
}

ROLE --> R
STORY --> PS
PROF --> SUM
PROF --> DOM
PROF --> STK
PROF --> THM

package "Consumed by (M:*)" {
  [summarize] as SUMM
  [commit-group\nclassify + compose] as CG
  [report\nfold merge] as REP
  [prepare] as PRE
  [final\nIMPACT + Role Narrative] as FIN
}

BLOCK --> SUMM
BLOCK --> CG
BLOCK --> REP
BLOCK --> PRE
BLOCK --> FIN

note bottom of BLOCK
  **Purpose:**
  • interpret patches in light of what the project is
  • avoid questions README/story already answer
  • frame **questions** by seniority (§8)
  **Never** use role to inflate impact
end note

note bottom of SUMM
  If project.json missing at model step:
  CLI **warns**, continues with empty context
  (same as pre-init behavior)
end note

@enduml


@startuml preconditions-role-questions
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false

title Role-aware **questions** — how init role shapes later outputs (§0, §8)

map "Question emphasis by role" as ROLEMAP {
  Principal Developer => system-wide trade-offs,\ncross-team boundaries,\nlong-term architectural consequences,\nproduction adoption at org scale
  Staff Developer => design ownership across subsystems,\nplatform direction,\nintegration with adjacent systems
  Senior Developer => feature/design ownership,\ncustomer or product driver,\nreplacing manual processes,\nmentoring or review scope
  Junior Developer => assigned vs self-directed work,\nlearning context, scope of autonomy,\nwho reviewed or unblocked
}

note bottom of ROLEMAP
  Questions target what **Git cannot know**:
  ownership, intent, production usage, customer driver, …
  Role shapes **which gaps to ask about**,
  not how impressive the work sounds.
end note

@enduml
